Working style request:
Operate like the prior chat did during most of the ux-refinement branch:
- Make small, targeted commits directly to the active GitHub branch when asked.
- Before editing, fetch the relevant file from GitHub.
- Preserve existing architecture and naming unless there is a strong reason to refactor.
- Avoid broad rewrites unless explicitly requested.
- Give concise commit summaries after changes.
- Include quick test instructions after each commit.
- Do not over-ask for confirmation when the request is clear.
- Be careful with mobile/desktop distinctions.
- Keep the user’s design intent primary: fantasy parchment atlas UI, readable, gameable, DM-friendly, not over-engineered.
- When uncertain about UI interpretation, make the most conservative implementation and explain what assumption was made.
- Avoid breaking established layout patterns, especially Codex detail page consistency.

Project overview:
This is a fantasy campaign atlas / codex app built on a Leaflet image map of Kadesh, with a Google Sheet backend. The map is the source of the geographic experience, and the Codex is the database/browser layer over that map. It is intended primarily as a DM-facing tool, with possible future expansion into controlled player-facing views only if account/access complexity becomes worth it.

Important current architecture:
- Data is loaded from published Google Sheets.
- Codex pages include:
  - Hex detail pages
  - POI index/detail pages
  - NPC index/detail pages
  - Region index/detail pages
  - Search page
- POIs, NPCs, Regions, Hexes are linked through reference IDs.
- POI groups were added to support large settlements/complexes spanning multiple hexes.

Major changelog from ux-refinement branch:

1. Mobile Codex UX
- Fixed scroll/fade behavior around mobile Codex content.
- Search results on mobile now use modal popovers rather than cramped internal nested scrollboxes.
- Mobile search input now blurs on Enter/search so the mobile keyboard closes.
- Mobile OS/back button behavior was improved:
  - within Codex, OS back behaves like internal Codex back
  - map side panel can close back to map
  - no map-panel history stack was added
- Back/close button sizing and glyph treatment were refined.
- Mobile back/map button text was removed and replaced with icon-only behavior.
- Mobile popup/hex tooltip now has a bottom action row:
  - `Details` button on the left, about 2/3 width
  - `×` close button on the right, about 1/3 width
  - close clears selected hex and closes popup

2. Search UX
- Search results order was adjusted so Hexes and Regions positions were swapped as requested.
- Mobile search results now use larger modal-style result panels matching filter/sort popup styling.
- Search result modals overlay the bottom nav buttons.
- Search buckets still include POIs, NPCs, Regions, Hexes.
- POI group deduping was implemented in Search:
  - grouped child POIs collapse into a single `poi-group` result under POIs
  - group result opens the POI group detail page
  - labels include total mapped area count, population, NPC count, and matching mapped area count
  - direct search over POI_Groups fields was added:
    - POI_Group_ID
    - POI_Group_Name
    - Group_Type
    - Population
    - Lore
    - DM_Journal

3. POI Groups
Added a new Google Sheet tab / data source:

POI_Groups:
