Published link used for POI_Groups:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vQ0ads-k6v3CiG58JEZkZa7sya_IqLMBiUTh0IfnKOGeWCmbbw9qLJL9KITnd_GadRzMVz_e0otMzaD/pubhtml?gid=1000348883&single=true

Data architecture additions:
- `db.raw.poiGroups`
- `db.poiGroupsById`
- `db.poisByGroupId`

Helper behavior:
- POI groups allow large settlements / complexes to span multiple mapped POI rows without showing as duplicate major POIs.
- Individual child POIs remain real records and still open as individual mapped areas.
- Grouped child POIs show `Part of: [Group Name]`.
- Group population overrides child POI population conceptually.
- Child POI detail pages no longer show population if part of a group.
- Hex POI lists do not show child population; instead they show:
  - `Part of: [Group Name] • Pop. [formatted population]`
- Population numbers are now formatted with commas.

POI group UI:
- Main POI index collapses grouped POIs into a single visible group entry.
- Group detail pages show:
  - type
  - population
  - mapped areas count
  - NPCs associated with grouped POIs
  - mapped areas list
  - group lore/journal panels
- Mapped Areas list on group detail pages now resembles POI list formatting, but excludes population and includes NPC count.
- Grouped child POI breadcrumbs now show:
  - Codex / Points of Interest / [Group Name] / [Mapped Area]
- Group page breadcrumbs show:
  - Codex / Points of Interest / [Group Name]

POI group behavior intentionally preserved:
- On Hex detail pages, clicking a grouped child POI still opens the child/mapped-area POI page, not the group page.
- This was explicitly preferred because the hex contains the specific mapped area, while breadcrumb/Part of links provide upward navigation.

4. Reference ID cleanup
POI IDs were normalized:
- SET-XXX style settlement IDs were converted to POI-XXXX style.
- Existing POI-XXX entries also gained an additional leading zero.
- Haunchrest Inn was assigned a uniform POI ID.
- NPC Home_ID_Ref values were updated based on the new mapping.
- The app should assume POI_IDs are now uniform POI-style IDs.
- Future write capability should generate the next highest sequential POI ID.

5. Backend/write-capability notes for later
Future app-to-Google-Sheet write capability was discussed but deferred as a much later stage.
Important guidance:
- Required fields are mostly nailed down.
- Reference IDs should be generated by checking the existing highest sequential value and incrementing.
- Avoid committing generated IDs for unfinished records if possible.
- Consider record states later, e.g. draft/finalized, but do not overbuild now.
- DM-only write UI is preferred.
- Player access control would probably require user accounts and is out-of-scope unless the project becomes much larger.
- For grouped POIs, future creation UI should allow:
  - no group
  - choose existing group
  - create new group
  - if creating new group, dynamically generate/input group ID and group name
- Group IDs are intentionally semantic, e.g. ERIKOL, TORGOS, GRANDABURG, not sequential. They are invisible on frontend and act as stable keys.

6. Region index and region detail changes
Regions are the next major focus.

Already implemented:
- Region index now renders as a 3-column desktop tile grid.
- Region tiles are hard-sorted A–Z by Region_Name, fallback Region_ID.
- Tiles are square.
- Tile layout:
  - top 2/3 image/placeholder thumbnail area
  - bottom 1/3 mostly opaque info panel
- Tile info includes:
  - region name
  - hex count
  - deduped POI count
  - mapped area count when relevant
  - NPC count
- Region tiles open the region detail page.
- Region tile image support uses the same image helper as detail pages.

Region detail page currently:
- Restructured to roughly match NPC/POI detail pages.
- Top header includes:
  - square image thumbnail
  - summary metadata
  - terrain profile right-aligned
- Bottom sections currently remain mostly as-is:
  - Region Notes
  - Points of Interest
  - NPCs
  - Hexes

Important: Region detail still needs a lot of work. User explicitly said Region work is next.

