9. Mobile/responsive caution
The user has asked several times about avoiding discrepancies across different mobile devices.
Guidance:
- Use stable viewport-relative sizing carefully.
- Avoid assumptions based solely on one mobile device.
- Prefer CSS that allows safe overflow/scrolling.
- Avoid nested scroll areas on mobile unless absolutely necessary.
- Watch browser chrome / OS element effects on viewport height.
- Consider mobile-specific overrides when desktop-first region layouts get too cramped.

